stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> IDLE
    IDLE --> PARSING: statement received
    PARSING --> BINDING: AST created
    BINDING --> MDL_REQUESTED: need table metadata
    MDL_REQUESTED --> MDL_GRANTED: compatible metadata lock
    MDL_REQUESTED --> MDL_WAITING: DDL or conflicting statement
    MDL_WAITING --> MDL_GRANTED: grant
    MDL_WAITING --> FAILED: timeout, killed, or victim

    MDL_GRANTED --> DICT_PINNED: pin TableDefinition
    DICT_PINNED --> PLAN_OPEN: build and open PlanNode tree
    PLAN_OPEN --> STORAGE_CURSOR_OPEN: open StorageCursor
    STORAGE_CURSOR_OPEN --> ROW_LOCK_WAIT: locking read or DML conflict
    STORAGE_CURSOR_OPEN --> ROW_AVAILABLE: nonlocking read or lock granted
    ROW_LOCK_WAIT --> ROW_LOCK_GRANTED: LockManager grant
    ROW_LOCK_WAIT --> FAILED: deadlock victim or lock timeout
    ROW_LOCK_GRANTED --> RELOCATING: storage re-enters B+Tree
    RELOCATING --> ROW_AVAILABLE: row validated
    ROW_AVAILABLE --> PRODUCING_ROWS: filter and projection
    ROW_AVAILABLE --> MODIFYING: DML current row
    MODIFYING --> MTR_COMMITTING: storage page changes
    MTR_COMMITTING --> STATEMENT_CLEANUP: redo and memo release
    PRODUCING_ROWS --> STATEMENT_CLEANUP: result exhausted
    STATEMENT_CLEANUP --> TRANSACTION_END: autocommit or explicit commit
    STATEMENT_CLEANUP --> IDLE: transaction remains active
    TRANSACTION_END --> IDLE: release row locks and transaction MDL
    FAILED --> STATEMENT_CLEANUP: cleanup cursor and locks
    IDLE --> [*]

    note right of MDL_WAITING
        Executor holds only MDL wait slot.
        It must not hold page latch, row lock shard,
        file latch, MTR latch, or RecordCursor.
    end note

    note right of ROW_LOCK_WAIT
        Storage layer releases page latch and buffer fix
        before entering LockManager wait.
    end note

